modules.description: Provides functions to generate OCaml code from ATD (A Type Definition) files, including parsing, type conversion, and code emission. Works with ATD abstract syntax trees and OCaml module structures. Used to automate the creation of type-safe data serialization and deserialization code.

Generates OCaml code from ATD files using a custom command and integrates with the build system through path manipulation. Processes lists of values and applies transformations to generate output files. Handles build hooks to trigger code generation during the compilation process.
